<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Try PlanX Digital Planning</h1>

<div class="govuk-panel govuk-panel--confirmation ndx-walkthrough-value-prop">
  <h2 class="govuk-panel__title">
    15 to 20 minutes to experience PlanX
  </h2>
  <div class="govuk-panel__body">
    Log in as a service designer, browse planning flows, edit a flow in the drag-and-drop editor, and explore the data layer.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="govuk-inset-text ndx-walkthrough-reassurance">
  <strong class="govuk-!-font-size-24">No technical knowledge required</strong>
  <p class="govuk-body">
    This walkthrough guides you through <a href="https://www.planx.uk/" class="govuk-link">PlanX</a> as a service designer would use it.
    You'll log in, browse planning flows, make an edit, and preview the applicant experience.
    Perfect for planning managers, digital transformation leads, and anyone evaluating PlanX.
  </p>
</div>

<p class="govuk-body">
  <a href="https://www.planx.uk/" class="govuk-link">PlanX</a> is the open-source digital planning platform developed by <a href="https://opendigitalplanning.org/" class="govuk-link">Open Systems Lab</a> as part of the Open Digital Planning programme. It's used by 18+ UK councils including Lambeth, Southwark, Camden, and Buckinghamshire to create digital planning application flows that guide citizens through the submission process.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">What you'll do</h2>

<p class="govuk-body-l">
  In this 15 to 20 minute walkthrough, you'll:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Log in to PlanX</strong> — Find your credentials and access the PlanX editor (2 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Browse planning flows</strong> — See the NDX Demo Council team and explore householder and LDC flows (3 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Edit a flow</strong> — Open a flow, explore the drag-and-drop node editor, and make a change (5 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Preview the applicant experience</strong> — Use the preview to see what citizens see when they submit a planning application (3 minutes)
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Explore the data layer</strong> — Open the Hasura console, browse tables, and see the GraphQL API (2 minutes)
  </li>
</ol>

